Yep — the **layered / modular-monolith approach** you and Gemini converged on is the right direction for “solo-dev but professional-tier” *as long as* you treat it as an **audit + safety system** first, and a strategy second. The biggest failures in real-money trading bots almost never come from “bad z-score math”; they come from **data gaps/duplicates, hidden lookahead, wrong fees/filters, order-state bugs, and no kill-switch/observability**. Your proposed structure can absolutely support real-money trading — but only once the *safety/observability/backtest realism* work is first-class and *done before* live execution.

Below is a **book of work** (exhaustive checklist + sequencing) with **clear “complete when…” definitions** for every step, plus how to develop components **in isolation**.

